A new course at Harvard University this year will ensure that all students get more sleep, in an attempt to combat the growing machoculture in which it seems cool to study all night and drink a lot of caffeine.
A professor noted that the students of the world’s largest university often have no idea of the basic principles of caring for themselves.
Charles Czeisler, professor of sleep medicine at Harvard Medical School, a specialist at Brigham and Women's Hospital, set up the course. As far as he knows this is unique in the US.
